{\par \b Syntax:}\par IF test THEN command(s) [ELSE commands] END;\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Evaluates test. If test is true (non 0), executes command(s); otherwise, executes the comands in the ELSE clause nothing happens.\par
{\par \b Example:}\par IF A<1 \par THEN PRINT(&quot;A IS SMALLER THAN 1&quot;); \par ELSE PRINT(&quot;A IS LARGER THAN 1&quot;); \par END;\par }